# UIEventSystem

## Purpose
Performs hit-testing each frame and resolves the pointer to a single element (top-most input capture,
ADR 0005). For every enabled UI entity it computes the logical-canvas rect via recursive parent-chain
traversal and tests the mouse against it; the mouse arrives in window pixels and is converted into
logical-canvas units (divided by the UI scale factor from RendererConfigSingletonComponent) first, so
hit-testing matches rendering at any window resolution. Among all elements under the cursor it keeps
only the front-most (greatest nesting depth, later iteration winning ties) and emits one-frame hover,
click, and release events on that element only — never leaking to elements behind it. Each event
carries the hit element's UUID.

When the front-most element is interactive (carries an ImageComponent or TextComponent) it also raises
an in-frame UIInputCapturedInFrameEvent so gameplay systems can ignore a pointer interaction that
landed on UI; bare layout containers do not raise it, leaving gameplay pointer input working over empty
UI areas.

Guards on InputStateSingletonComponent and RendererConfigSingletonComponent presence; returns
immediately if either is absent.

## Input Components
| Component | Access |
|---|---|
| InputStateSingletonComponent | read |
| RendererConfigSingletonComponent | read |
| BaseComponent | read |
| LayoutContainerComponent | read |
| UIClipComponent | read |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| UIOnHoverOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted on the front-most element under the cursor |
| UIOnClickOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted on the front-most element when the left mouse button is pressed while hovering |
| UIOnReleaseOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted on the front-most element when the left mouse button is released while hovering; mutually exclusive with click per frame |
| UIInputCapturedInFrameEvent | add (inframe) | Raised when the front-most element is interactive (image/text); signals gameplay that UI owns the pointer this frame |
